to mixing bowl and cook <nobr>12 min\/100°C\/speed 4<\/nobr>. Remove basket with aid of spatula and transfer rice into a separate thermal serving bowl or other large bowl and cover to keep warm.","Reduce oven temperature to 160°C and roast pork for a further 20 minutes (160°C), or until tender and skin is crisp.","Transfer pork onto a chopping board and cut into pieces (approx. 3 cm) with a sharp knife and add to reserved sauce, then stir to combine. Sprinkle vindaloo with toasted cashews and serve with rice."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Curry mix","content":["2 tsp coriander seeds","1 tsp cumin seeds","2 cm cinnamon quill","4 whole cloves","2 cardamom pods","1 tsp black peppercorns","1 tsp dried chilli flakes","3 cm  piece fresh ginger, peeled","6 garlic cloves","½ tsp ground turmeric","1 pinch salt","1 tbsp olive oil","2 tsp apple cider vinegar"]},{"title":"Pork belly","content":["1000 g pork belly meat, boned, scored","2 brown onions (approx. 240 g), cut into halves","2 - 3 fresh bird's eye chillies, trimmed and cut into pieces","30 g olive oil","8 fresh curry leaves","1 tbsp soft dark brown sugar","1400 g water","1 tsp salt, plus extra for seasoning","200 g basmati rice","1 tsp black mustard seeds (see Tips)","50 g raw unsalted cashew nuts, toasted"]}],"id":"r115612","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-57bMOgzKRFk\/XZQvnWDvNII\/AAAAAAAAcdw\/iQkGFPlF06AG5Tkc6_pmr1g2e2WgKfqNwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_JSMKr75ckMvz9ueN.png","title":"Vindaloo pork","publishedAt":"2016-10-16T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"57.2 g","fat":"60.6 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"49.9 g","calories":"4119 kJ \/ 980 kcal"},"usefulItems":"large bowl, plastic wrap, roasting tray, aluminium foil, thermal serving bowl or other large bowl, wooden chopping board, refrigerator, oven","hintsAndTricks":["You can buy black mustard seeds from spice shops and online.","For a milder heat, replace bird's eye chillies with fresh red chillies (deseeded if preferred)."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","5h 10m","4 portions"]}